OL,3,CInfected blood inquiry: What were the
OL,4,Cmissed opportunities?
OL,6,FAt the time of writing, around 3,000
OL,7,Fpeople are believed to have died as a
OL,8,Fresult of the mistreatment - among
OL,9,Fthem 380 children.
OL,11,F"This disaster was not an accident.
OL,12,FThe infections happened because those
OL,13,Fin authority - doctors, the blood
OL,14,Fservices and successive governments -
OL,15,Fdid not put patient safety first," the
OL,16,Fchair of the inquiry, former judge Sir
OL,17,FBrian Langstaff, said in a statement
OL,18,Fissued alongside the report.
OL,20,FThe inquiry process has no scope to
OL,21,Fdetermine civil or criminal liability.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/14
