OL,3,CInfected blood inquiry: What were the
OL,4,Cmissed opportunities?
OL,6,FThe fatal risks of Hepatitis C, for
OL,7,Fexample, were already known since
OL,8,FWorld War Two, where the blood-borne
OL,9,Fvirus spread easily among soldiers who
OL,10,Fwere being treated in unsanitary field
OL,11,Fhospitals.
OL,13,FBy the mid-1980s, Aids emerged as a
OL,14,Ffurther threat to the safety of blood
OL,15,Fsupply and blood products, which the
OL,16,FDepartment of Health and Social
OL,17,FSecurity (DHSS) was "well aware" of,
OL,18,Faccording to the report.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G4/14
