OL,3,CInfected blood inquiry: What were the
OL,4,Cmissed opportunities?
OL,6,FAs a result, blood products were
OL,7,Fmostly imported from the United
OL,8,FStates, which took blood from high-
OL,9,Frisk paid donors, such as prisoners
OL,10,Fand drug addicts.
OL,12,FBy mid-1982, the government was aware
OL,13,Fthat the imported commercial blood
OL,14,Fproducts - known as factor 8
OL,15,Fconcentrate - carried a high risk of
OL,16,Fhepatitis and were less safe than
OL,17,Fdomestic treatments, of which there
OL,18,Fshould have been a sufficient supply.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/14
