OL,3,CInfected blood inquiry: What were the
OL,4,Cmissed opportunities?
OL,6,FDespite this, it still decided not to
OL,7,Fsuspend the importations in 1983, and
OL,8,Fincreased the size of pools to
OL,9,Fmanufacture the treatment, instead -
OL,10,Fmarkedly increasing the risks of viral
OL,11,Ftransmission even more.
OL,13,F3. Failure to stop prison donations
OL,14,Fand conduct rigorous donor selection
OL,16,FWhile much of the focus of the inquiry
OL,17,Fwas on blood products imported from
OL,18,Fthe US, the report also makes clear
OL,19,Fthere were issues with domestic prison
OL,20,Fdonations.
