OL,3,CInfected blood inquiry: What were the
OL,4,Cmissed opportunities?
OL,6,FBlood collection from prisons was a
OL,7,Fcommon practice in the UK throughout
OL,8,Fthe 1970s and early 1980s.
OL,10,FThis was despite reported evidence
OL,11,Fthere is a much higher incidence of
OL,12,Fhepatitis among prisoners than amongst
OL,13,Fthe rest of the donor population.
OL,15,FYet, no action was taken to stop
OL,16,Fdonations or discourage them.
OL,18,FThe report says that UK blood services
OL,19,F"failed to ensure sufficiently
OL,20,Frigorous donor selection and screening
OL,21,Fof blood donors."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G8/14
